stories.title: South Africa win sets up series finale
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v South Africa, 4th ODI, Rawalpindi
stories.summary: Herschelle Gibbs' flourish at the top of the innings and Jacques Kallis' lesson in middle-order stability helped South Africa to a six-wicket win, and so level the five-match series and set up the decider  on Sunday
stories.byline: The Wisden Bulletin by Siddhartha Vaidyanathan
